    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Still no luck with Powerpoint. But here are the color schemes that appear to be better choices according to ColorBrewer.\r\n\r\nhttp://colorbrewer2.org/?type=diverging&scheme=PuOr&n=4, colorblind-friendly\r\n230,97,1\r\n253,184,99\r\n178,171,210\r\n94,60,153\r\n\r\nThis is what it looks like in color and in grayscale:\r\n![color scheme saturated](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/295338/23591761/db8c8668-01f5-11e7-8d99-648c73d969e2.png)\r\n![color scheme](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/295338/23591758/d5f71010-01f5-11e7-9176-ed196d30c0a2.png)\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nhttp://colorbrewer2.org/?type=diverging&scheme=Spectral&n=5, not colorbind friendly, but +1 color\r\n215,25,28\r\n253,174,97\r\n255,255,191\r\n171,221,164\r\n43,131,186\r\n\r\nAlthough this one is supposed to be \"photocopy friendly\", if I remove the saturation 2 of the colours look the same.\r\n![color2](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/295338/23591806/8a998cd2-01f6-11e7-99ee-703d3fa18352.png)\r\n![color2-desaturated](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/295338/23591810/90b4e85a-01f6-11e7-93ec-ff48ad6127c0.png)\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nPerhaps it is me, or my monitor  - I am wondering if others can relate to my perception of the samples above."
