    "body": "@ralienpp So here is what I think will be a challenge here.  Consider these colors used in the `pd.melt()` example:\r\n![image](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/15113894/23969660/94ad1c76-099d-11e7-9473-4e3884762447.png)\r\n\r\nThere are 9 colors here, 3 shades of grey, 2 shades each of green, orange, and blue.  The \"darker\" colors are used to indicate column names in the source data, that then become part of the data in the resulting operation.  I don't know how we maintain the color relationship in black-and-white to indicate the dark/light shading relationship.\r\n\r\nWhat I would need from you is something that said for each of those 9 colors, what RGB to use.  Can you do that?\r\n"
